      <head>Friedrich Ernst Koch</head>
      <div>
        <p>German composer, cellist, and teacher. </p>
        <p>Koch studied cello with Hausmann and music theory with Bargiel. He taught cello privately
          from 1901. He composed operas, oratorios, two symphonies, chamber and choral works. </p>
      </div>
      <div>
        <head>Koch and Schenker</head>
        <p>In December 1919, in response to a question, Schenker advised <ref cRef="dahms_walter">Walter Dahms</ref> to seek instruction from Friedrich Ernst Koch in preference to <ref cRef="halm_august">August Halm</ref> (OJ 3/1 , p. 2192, December 15, 1919), but does not
          spell out the reasons in his diary entry. </p>
      </div>
